UE5 Blueprint File - BP_NPC_DialogueComponent_v01
================================================

This is a Blueprint Component that extends UDialogueComponent (C++ class).

To create this blueprint in Unreal Engine 5.2+:
1. Right-click in Content Browser
2. Search for "UDialogueComponent"
3. Select "BP_NPC_DialogueComponent_v01"
4. Click "Create"

Components:
- DialogueTree (Array of FDialogueNode)
- DialogueHistory (Array of FString)
- Reputation (Float)
- CurrentState (Enum: Idle, Active, Processing, Complete)
- CurrentDialogueID (String)
- IsQuestGiver (Boolean)
- QuestIDs (Array of FString)
- AvailableQuests (Array of FString)

Functions:
- InitializeDialogue(FString, TArray<FString>)
- StartDialogue(AActor*)
- ProcessDialogue(FString)
- EndDialogue()
- UpdateReputation(float)
- CheckQuestAvailability(FString)
- GetAvailableQuests() -> TArray<FString>
- GetReputation() -> Float
- GetCurrentState() -> ENPCDialogueState

Note: This blueprint must be compiled after adding components.
Note: This blueprint requires dialogue data assets from designers.
Note: This blueprint requires dialogue widget from UI designers.